                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d286">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 818.00/487</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leavell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-18T12:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 18, 1918, noon.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your September 13, noon. Casa Miglia has arrived, and is accredited to this
                    Government as the regular Costa Rican Chargé d’Affaires, and also elected a
                    member of the Central American International Bureau, as I am informed, by the
                    Minister of State. Nevertheless, in my coining interview with the President, I
                    shall avail myself of the opportunity to make the intimation according to your
                    instructions; meanwhile I had asked Consul Gozo [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] to
                    caution consular agent at port as to any such shipments being taken on an
                    American vessel.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leavell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
